<EventsDetail ID="x48876" Name="Mystery Dinner" Layout="general_activities.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Event Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Mystery Dinner -  Misty Island</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">New Storyline</Abstract><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Event Details" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<div>This decription is from last semester to give you an idea of what to expect. We will be announcing the new story line soon.</div>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Description:</span></strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; And this is how the Misty Island Mystery Dinner started...</p>
<p>Gertrud Hesseldorf, the owner of Misty Island, invited her favorite students from the Bethlehem University for a ten-year reunion on her island.&nbsp; All eight students were excited and quickly gathered at Misty Island.&nbsp; The students included Monica Gestetner, Dave Bagshaw, Melinda Lehman, Ken Muller, John Allured, Stephanie Stephens, Rick Tuttle and Kristen Potter.&nbsp;</p>
<p>When the students and Gertrud established the schedule for the next week, they all left to explore the island. &nbsp;Later that night, a Radio Transmission call was made from the island for an emergency.&nbsp; Find out what, and "who dunnit".</p>
<p>It is up to you to solve this mystery!&nbsp; Play the characters on the island and try to find out who the murderer is.&nbsp; Dress up as a character, have dinner served to you, and play a mystery game!&nbsp; This Misty Island Mystery Dinner is full of thrills.&nbsp; Come join the crime solving fun!!!</p>
